Conflicts: kmscon
Replaces: kmscon
Description: KMS terminal emulator with Korean (Hangul) input support
 kmscon is a simple terminal emulator based on Linux kernel mode
 setting (KMS). It is an attempt to replace the in-kernel VT
 implementation with a userspace console.
 .
 This build adds a generic input method (IM) abstraction layer and
 Korean (Hangul) input support via libhangul, with dubeolsik/sebeolsik
 keyboard layouts and Han/Eng toggle key. Extensible for future CJK
 input methods (Chinese, Japanese).
 .
 Also includes a fix for a use-after-free SEGV crash on VT switch or
 DPMS wake-up, and corrected freetype CJK font sizing.
